      "id": "q2",
      "question": "Define BPE?",
      "answer": "Byte-Pair Encoding (BPE) is the dominant tokenization algorithm in modern large language models. Originally a data compression algorithm (Gage 1994), it was adapted for natural language processing by Sennrich et al. (2016). The tokenizer is trained separately on your text corpus before model training begins. It starts with a base vocabulary of individual units like characters or bytes, then counts all adjacent token pairs and merges the most frequent ones into a single new token until reaching a target vocabulary size.",
